thnic groups reconcile through reasoned, respectful, and empathetic deliberation of a difficult legacy. She finds that expression of ethnic difference plays a role in good-quality deliberation across ethnic lines, while revealed intraethnic divisions help deliberators expand moral horizons previously narrowed by conflict. In the process, people forge bonds of solidarity and offset divisive identity politics that bears upon their deliberations.Reconciliation by Stealth shows us the importance of theoretical and methodological innovation in capturing how transitional justice can promote reconciliation, and points to the untapped potential of deliberative problem-solving to repair relationships fractured by conflict.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEthnic conflictzFormer Yugoslav republics. 0aReconciliationzFormer Yugoslav republics. 0aTransitional justicezFormer Yugoslav republics. 0aWar crimeszFormer Yugoslav republics. 0aYugoslav War, 1991-1995xPeace. 4aCULTURAL STUDIES. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aSOCIOLOGY & SOCIAL SCIENCE. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / European.2bisacsh  atransitional justice, deliberation in divided societies, identity politics, transitional justice in the Balkans, ethnic identity and post-conflict reconciliation, justice and war crimes, reconciliation and peace in the Balkans, post-conflict justice negotiations.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023 Englishz978311131925408iTitle is part of eBook